# Appwrite Real-time Subscriptions

You can subscribe to multiple channels in a single `client.subscribe()` call by passing an array of channel strings.

## Exact Channel Strings

```javascript
const unsubscribe = client.subscribe([
  'databases.<databaseId>.collections.<collectionId>.documents',
  'buckets.<bucketId>.files'
], (response) => {
  console.log(response);
});
```

## Channel Format Breakdown

| Resource Type | Channel String Format |
|---------------|----------------------|
| **Database Documents** | `databases.[databaseId].collections.[collectionId].documents` |
| **Storage Files** | `buckets.[bucketId].files` |

## Complete Example

```javascript
const client = new Client()
  .setEndpoint('https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
  .setProject('YOUR_PROJECT_ID');

const unsubscribe = client.subscribe(
  [
    'databases.myDatabase.collections.myCollection.documents',
    'buckets.myBucket.files'
  ],
  (response) => {
    // Handle both database and storage events
    console.log('Event:', response.events);
    console.log('Payload:', response.payload);
  }
);
```

## Notes

- Replace `<databaseId>`, `<collectionId>`, and `<bucketId>` with your actual IDs
- The callback receives a `response` object with `events` (array of event strings) and `payload` (the changed document/file)
- Call `unsubscribe()` when you no longer need the subscription

# Appwrite Realtime Subscription for Documents and Files

Here's a complete example showing how to subscribe to both document changes and file uploads simultaneously using the Appwrite Web SDK:

## Installation

```bash
npm install appwrite
```

## Complete Code Example

```javascript
import { Client, Databases, Storage, ID } from 'appwrite';

// Initialize the client
const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('YOUR_PROJECT_ID');

// Initialize services
const databases = new Databases(client);
const storage = new Storage(client);

// Constants
const DATABASE_ID = 'your-database-id';
const COLLECTION_ID = 'your-collection-id';
const BUCKET_ID = 'your-bucket-id';

// ============================================
// SUBSCRIBE TO REALTIME EVENTS
// ============================================

// Subscribe to database document changes
const unsubscribeDocuments = client.subscribe(
    `databases.${DATABASE_ID}.collections.${COLLECTION_ID}.documents`,
    (response) => {
        handleDocumentEvent(response);
    }
);

// Subscribe to file storage uploads
const unsubscribeFiles = client.subscribe(
    `buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files`,
    (response) => {
        handleFileEvent(response);
    }
);

// ============================================
// EVENT HANDLERS
// ============================================

function handleDocumentEvent(response) {
    const { events, payload, channels } = response;

    // Determine the event type from the events array
    const eventType = events[0]; // e.g., "databases.[ID].collections.[ID].documents.[ID].create"

    console.log('📄 Document Event:', eventType);
    console.log('Payload:', payload);

    if (eventType.includes('.create')) {
        console.log('✅ New document created!');
        handleNewDocument(payload);
    } 
    else if (eventType.includes('.update')) {
        console.log('✏️ Document updated!');
        handleDocumentUpdate(payload);
    } 
    else if (eventType.includes('.delete')) {
        console.log('🗑️ Document deleted!');
        handleDocumentDelete(payload);
    }
}

function handleFileEvent(response) {
    const { events, payload } = response;

    const eventType = events[0];

    console.log('📁 File Event:', eventType);
    console.log('File Info:', payload);

    if (eventType.includes('.create')) {
        console.log('✅ New file uploaded!');
        handleFileUpload(payload);
    } 
    else if (eventType.includes('.update')) {
        console.log('✏️ File updated!');
        handleFileUpdate(payload);
    } 
    else if (eventType.includes('.delete')) {
        console.log('🗑️ File deleted!');
        handleFileDelete(payload);
    }
}

// ============================================
// SPECIFIC HANDLERS FOR EACH EVENT TYPE
// ============================================

// Document handlers
function handleNewDocument(document) {
    console.log('Processing new document:', document.$id);
    // Custom logic: send notification, update UI, etc.
}

function handleDocumentUpdate(document) {
    console.log('Document updated:', document.$id, document);
    // Custom logic: refresh data, show toast, etc.
}

function handleDocumentDelete(document) {
    console.log('Document deleted:', document.$id);
    // Custom logic: remove from UI, etc.
}

// File handlers
function handleFileUpload(file) {
    console.log('Processing uploaded file:', file.name);
    // Custom logic: generate thumbnail, scan for viruses, etc.

    // Access file preview URL
    const previewUrl = client.getPreview(
        BUCKET_ID,
        file.$id,
        100, // width
        100  // height
    );
    console.log('Preview URL:', previewUrl);
}

function handleFileUpdate(file) {
    console.log('File updated:', file.name);
}

function handleFileDelete(file) {
    console.log('File deleted:', file.name);
}

// ============================================
// CLEANUP - UNSUBSCRIBE WHEN NO LONGER NEEDED
// ============================================

function cleanupSubscriptions() {
    unsubscribeDocuments();
    unsubscribeFiles();
    console.log('✅ Unsubscribed from all realtime events');
}

// Call cleanup when user logs out or leaves the page
// window.addEventListener('beforeunload', cleanupSubscriptions);
```

## Event Channel Patterns

| Resource | Channel Pattern |
|----------|-----------------|
| All documents in a collection | `databases.[ID].collections.[ID].documents` |
| Specific document | `databases.[ID].collections.[ID].documents.[ID]` |
| All files in a bucket | `buckets.[ID].files` |
| Specific file | `buckets.[ID].files.[ID]` |
| Files in a specific folder | `buckets.[ID].files.[ID]/[folderPath]` |

## Event Types

- **`.create`** - New document/file created
- **`.update`** - Existing document/file updated
- **`.delete`** - Document/file deleted

## Key Points

1. **Separate subscriptions** - Each `client.subscribe()` call creates an independent connection
2. **Event routing** - Check the `events` array to determine what type of change occurred
3. **Payload access** - The `payload` property contains the actual document/file data
4. **Cleanup** - Always unsubscribe when the component unmounts to prevent memory leaks

