```

## Key Points

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Bucket permissions** | Control access at the bucket level for all files within it |
| **File permissions** | Only enforced when `fileSecurity` is `true` on the bucket |
| **`getFilePreview`** | Returns a **URL object** (not a network request) — works only for image files |
| **`getFileView`** | Use this for non-image files or to get the original without transforms |
| **`getFileDownload`** | Returns a URL that triggers a browser download |

> **Permission precedence:** When `fileSecurity` is `true`, access is granted if **either** bucket-level **or** file-level permissions allow it. When `false`, only bucket-level permissions are checked.

# Appwrite Realtime: Document Changes & File Uploads

Here's how to subscribe to multiple realtime channels and handle each event type differently using the Appwrite Web SDK:

## Setup & Subscribe

```javascript
import { Client, Databases, Storage } from 'appwrite';

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('YOUR_PROJECT_ID');

const databases = new Databases(client);
const storage = new Storage(client);

const DATABASE_ID = 'myDatabase';
const COLLECTION_ID = 'myCollection';
const BUCKET_ID = 'myBucket';

// Subscribe to BOTH channels simultaneously
const unsubscribe = client.subscribe(
    [
        `databases.${DATABASE_ID}.collections.${COLLECTION_ID}.documents`,
        `buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files`
    ],
    (response) => {
        // --- Handle Document Events ---
        if (
            response.events.includes(
                `databases.${DATABASE_ID}.collections.${COLLECTION_ID}.documents.*.create`
            )
        ) {
            console.log('📄 Document CREATED:', response.payload);
            handleDocumentCreate(response.payload);
        }

        if (
            response.events.includes(
                `databases.${DATABASE_ID}.collections.${COLLECTION_ID}.documents.*.update`
            )
        ) {
            console.log('✏️ Document UPDATED:', response.payload);
            handleDocumentUpdate(response.payload);
        }

        if (
            response.events.includes(
                `databases.${DATABASE_ID}.collections.${COLLECTION_ID}.documents.*.delete`
            )
        ) {
            console.log('🗑️ Document DELETED:', response.payload);
            handleDocumentDelete(response.payload);
        }

        // --- Handle File Events ---
        if (
            response.events.includes(
                `buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files.*.create`
            )
        ) {
            console.log('📁 File UPLOADED:', response.payload);
            handleFileUpload(response.payload);
        }

        if (
            response.events.includes(
                `buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files.*.update`
            )
        ) {
            console.log('📝 File UPDATED:', response.payload);
            handleFileUpdate(response.payload);
        }

        if (
            response.events.includes(
                `buckets.${BUCKET_ID}.files.*.delete`
            )
        ) {
            console.log('🗑️ File DELETED:', response.payload);
            handleFileDelete(response.payload);
        }
    }
);

// --- Event Handlers ---

function handleDocumentCreate(document) {
    // e.g., append to a list in the UI
    const list = document.getElementById('doc-list');
    const item = document.createElement('li');
    item.textContent = `New: ${document.name} (ID: ${document.$id})`;
    list?.appendChild(item);
}

function handleDocumentUpdate(document) {
    // e.g., update existing element in the UI
    const existing = document.getElementById(`doc-${document.$id}`);
    if (existing) {
        existing.textContent = `Updated: ${document.name}`;
    }
}

function handleDocumentDelete(document) {
    // e.g., remove element from the UI
    const existing = document.getElementById(`doc-${document.$id}`);
    existing?.remove();
}

function handleFileUpload(file) {
    console.log(`File "${file.name}" (${file.sizeOriginal} bytes) uploaded.`);
    // e.g., display a thumbnail or download link
    const preview = storage.getFilePreview(BUCKET_ID, file.$id);
    console.log('Preview URL:', preview);
}

function handleFileUpdate(file) {
    console.log(`File "${file.name}" metadata updated.`);
}

function handleFileDelete(file) {
    console.log(`File "${file.$id}" was deleted.`);
}

// --- Cleanup: unsubscribe when no longer needed ---
// e.g., on component unmount or page navigation
// unsubscribe();
```

## Key Concepts

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Multiple channels** | Pass an array of channel strings to `client.subscribe()` |
| **Event matching** | Use `response.events.includes(...)` to distinguish event types |
| **Event format** | `databases.{dbId}.collections.{colId}.documents.*.{action}` for docs, `buckets.{bucketId}.files.*.{action}` for files |
| **Actions** | `create`, `update`, `delete` |
| **Payload** | `response.payload` contains the full document or file object |
| **Cleanup** | Call the returned `unsubscribe()` function to close the connection |

## Important Notes

- **Authentication**: The user must have **read permissions** on the target collection/bucket to receive realtime events.
- **Single connection**: Appwrite multiplexes all subscriptions over a **single WebSocket connection**, so subscribing to multiple channels is efficient.
- **Unsubscribe**: Always call `unsubscribe()` during cleanup (e.g., in React's `useEffect` return, or Vue's `onUnmounted`) to prevent memory leaks.
